alike, but is said to pass as one becomes accustomed to the local food. ginger is effective against nausea, though it does not kill bacteria. even in the cities, chinese people do not drink water straight from the tap, and you should not either. all hotels (even boats!) provide either a thermos flask of boiled water in your room (refillable by your floor attendant) or - more commonly - a kettle you can use to do it yourself. generally, tap water is safe to drink after boiling. purified drinking water in bottles is available everywhere, and is generally quite cheap. 